common_issues.title: JetBrains plugin installation issue
common_issues.description: Users are unable to install a specific JetBrains plugin because it's not found in the JetBrains Marketplace.  This issue is occurring on macOS with Pieces OS version 12.2.1 and is related to an Early Access Program feature.  The plugin might not be published or accessible yet.  Check for updates or contact support.

### Kindly describe the bug and include as much detail as possible on what you were doing so we can reproduce the bug.

I'd like to install a JetBrains plugin, but it doesn't exist in the JetBrains Marketplace.
Error generating summary: 404 Publisher Model `projects/pi3c3s-cloud-server/locations/us-east1/publishers/google/models/gemini-pro` was not found or your project does not have access to it. Please ensure you are using a valid model version. For more information, see: https://cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/generative-ai/docs/learn/model-versions

recommendations: Investigate and resolve JetBrains plugin installation issue on macOS (Pieces OS 12.2.1). Check plugin publishing status and ensure its availability in JetBrains Marketplace.
Provide support documentation or communication addressing the JetBrains plugin installation issue for macOS users in the Early Access Program.
Monitor and address the activity level of ticket #849 regarding the JetBrains plugin issue.
